FBIS4-48513 "drafr098_c_94007" FBIS-AFR-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Intruders Spotted at Home of ANC Secretary General Intruders Spotted at Home of ANC Secretary General MB1905162394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1540 GMT 19 May 94 MB1905162394 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Text] Johannesburg May 19 SAPA -- Four masked men were on Thursday morning chased from the Berario, Johannesburg home of African National Congress Secretary-General Cyril Ramaphosa, police reported. A security guard became suspicious when the four white men drove past the house in a red 16-valve Golf without registration plates at 11.40AM. He opened fire with a shotgun when two of the men jumped over the back garden wall. It is not known if either of the men was hit. Anyone with information that might assist the police should telephone a Lt Nel at 678-4445.
